uh now something may be fully accepted by faith and yet may be empty hollow and false but something else may be fully accepted by faith and yet may be factual true and unmistaken and so he goes through the other types of misunderstood ways of thinking about things or coming to believe in things it is not proper that a wise man who preserves truth to come to a definite conclusion only this is true

167
